  "title": "Electrical Fitter",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Install components and wire connections, accordingly to schematics to ensure proper terminations and secure wiring.</li><li>Study drawings or specifications to determine work requirements.</li><li>Adhere to safety protocols procedures and electrical codes.</li><li>Identify and report any issues or deviations from specifications.</li><li>Perform site work and field services when required.</li><li>Ensure all standards and guidelines comply with the company’s ISO requirements.</li><li>Ensure all productivity and efficiency is kept at the highest level</li><li>Any other Ad-hoc duties assigned</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>NITEC / Higher NITEC / Diploma in Electrical Engineering or related field.</li><li><strong>Able to do power cable or control cable wiring</strong>.</li><li>Relevant experience in electrical fitting, installation and maintenance.</li><li>Strong knowledge of electrical systems, schematics, and safety standards.</li><li>Ability to use electrical measuring and testing instruments.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Interested applicants are invited to submit a detailed resume including:</p><ul><li>Current and expected salary</li><li>Earliest availability</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>",
